        "created_at": "2020-12-09T02:54:18.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3308921&amp;iNote=8813456\"><strong>2017 Henri Germain et Fils Meursault</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Meursault (12/8/2020)</em><br>\nImmediately expressive nose bursting with orchard fruits, peach pit, wet stone, lime peel, vanillin, white flowers. Palate shows ripe white peach, pineapple and a tight minerality on a strong acidic backbone. Great balance that will only increase with some age. This is the top 2017 white village wine I\u2019ve had. <em><strong>(94 pts.)</strong></em></p>",
